|first2=Aaron P.|title=''Galanthus panjutinii'' ''sp. nov.'': a new name for an invalidly published species of ''Galanthus'' (Amaryllidaceae) from the northern Colchis area of Western Transcaucasia|journal=[[Phytotaxa]]|date=20 April 2012|volume=50|issue=1|pages=55|doi=10.11646/phytotaxa.50.1.5|url=http://citesbulbs.myspecies.info/sites/citesbulbs.myspecies.info/files/Zubov%20%26%20Davis%202012.pdf|ref=harv}}\n\n=== Websites ===\n\n* {{cite web|last1=Ellis|first1=Si\u00e2n|title=Snowdrops and Strange Galanthophiles|url=http://britishheritage.com/snowdrops-and-strange-galanthophiles/|website=British Heritage Travel|publisher=British Heritage Society|date=1 May 2010|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite web|title=Henry John Elwes|url=https://www.colesbournegardens.org.uk/about-us/henry-john-elwes.html|website=Colesbourne Park 'England's Greatest Snowdrop Garden'|publisher=Colesbourne Gardens LLP|date=2011|ref={{harvid|Colesbourne Park |2011}}}}\n* {{cite web|last1=Vigneron|first1=Pascal|title=Amaryllidaceae|url=http://www.amaryllidaceae.org//index.htm|website=Amaryllidaceae.org|accessdate=23 October 2014|language=French|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150104114211/http://www.amaryllidaceae.org/index.htm|archive-date=4 January 2015|url-status=dead}}\n* {{cite news|last1=Glanfield|first1=Emma|title=Bulbs go for \u00a3100 each in Great Snowdrop Rush as warmest year on record means Britain is blooming marvellous|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2925746/Bulbs-100-Great-Snowdrop-Rush-warmest-year-record-means-Britain-blooming-marvellous.html|newspaper=[[Daily Mail]]|accessdate=12 October 2016|date=25 January 2015}}\n* {{cite web|title=Snowdrop Week: Galanthus 'John Gray'|url=https://frustratedgardener.com/2015/02/09/snowdrop-week-galanthus-john-gray/|website=The Frustrated Gardener|accessdate=12 October 2016|date=9 February 2015}}\n* {{cite web|title=Snowdrops: An introduction|url=https://changinglifestyleblog.wordpress.com/2015/03/23/snowdrops-an-introduction/|date=23 