{"title_page": "Bukovina (Blansko District)", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name=Bukovina\n|settlement_type=Municipality\n|image_skyline=Bukovina 3.JPG\n|image_shield = Bukovina (Blansko) CoA.png\n|image_flag = Flag of Bukovina(okres Blansko).svg\n|subdivision_type=Country\n|subdivision_name={{CZE}}\n|subdivision_type1=[[Regions of the Czech Republic|Region]]\n|subdivision_name1=[[South Moravian Region|South Moravian]]\n|subdivision_type2=[[Districts of the Czech Republic|District]]\n|subdivision_name2=[[Blansko District|Blansko]]\n|coordinates = {{coord|49|17|56|N|16|46|39|E|region:CZ|display=inline,title}}\n|pushpin_map=Czech Republic|area_total_km2=2.73\n|population_total=337|population_as_of=2006\n|population_density_km2=auto\n|elevation_m=497\n|postal_code_type=Postal&nbsp;code|postal_code=679&nbsp;05\n|website=http://www.obecbukovina.cz\n}}\n\n'''Bukovina''' is a village and municipality (''[[obec]]'') in [[Blansko District]] in the [[South Moravian Region]] of the Czech Republic.\n\nThe municipality covers an area of {{convert|2.73|km2|sqmi}}, and has a population of 337 (as at 3&nbsp;July 2006).\n\nBukovina lies approximately {{convert|12|km|mi|0}} south-east of [[Blansko]], {{convert|17|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} north-east of [[Brno]], and {{convert|191|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} south-east of [[Prague]].\n\n==References==\n{{commons category|Bukovina (Blansko District)}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20071011015850/http://www.czso.cz/lexikon/mos_vdb.nsf/okresy/CZ0621 Czech Statistical Office: Municipalities of Blansko District]\n\n{{Blansko District}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bukovina}}\n[[Category:Villages in Blansko District]]\n\n\n{{SouthMoravia-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name=Bukovina\n|settlement_type=Municipality\n|image_skyline=Bukovina 3.JPG\n|image_shield = Bukovina (Blansko) CoA.png\n|image_flag = Flag of Bukovina(okres Blansko).svg\n|subdivision_type=Country\n|subdivision_name={{CZE}}\n|subdivision_type1=[[Region